The Partners for Legislative Agenda for Nigeria (PLAN), a coalition of civil society and youth groups, has commended President Muhammadu Buhari for reappointing Godwin Emefiele as governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) for another term of five years. The president has sent Emefiele’s name to the Senate for confirmation. PLAN’s Coordinator, Mallam Khalifa Bello Adamu, in a statement yesterday, said the act remained one of the dynamic moves of President Buhari and a symbolism of a new dawn where high premium is placed on hard work and competence. According to him, PLAN is in support of Emefiele’s reappointment strictly on the grounds of his prowess, non partisan posture and ability to rejuvenate the economy.  Buhari lauded for reappointing Emefiele as CBN governor Saraki reads Emefiele's reappointment letter Nomination of Emefiele good for Nigeria’s economy - Uba Sani Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin